7 (a) The Center shall:
8 (1) Work in consultation with the Governor’s Office of Crime Prevention,
9 Youth, and Victim Services or any successor agency, the Maryland State Police, and any
10 other relevant State or local agency to ensure a multidepartmental approach to reducing
11 firearm violence;
12 (2) Solicit and consider recommendations from:
13 (i) Communities disproportionately impacted by firearm violence;
14 (ii) Public health experts;
15 (iii) Individuals or organizations with expertise in firearm safety and
16 training; and
17 (iv) Any other experts, groups, or organizations as the executive
18 director determines appropriate and necessary; and
19 (3) (i) On or before May 1, 2025, submit a preliminary State Plan for a
20 Public Health Approach to Reducing Firearm Violence to guide the work of the Center to
21 the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the
22 General Assembly; and
23 (ii) On or before May 1, 2029, and every 4 years thereafter, submit a
24 State Strategic Plan for Firearm Violence Reduction Using Public Health Strategies to the
25 Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the General
26 Assembly.
27 (b) The Center may:
28 (1) Offer training and technical assistance to State and local agencies,
29 health care professionals, and community and faith–based organizations to increase
30 capacity to implement evidence–based firearm violence prevention and intervention
31 strategies;

